  "bio": "<p>Josue is only 17, but he has faced more challenges than many people do in a lifetime. He survived TB meningitis as a baby and was later diagnosed with cerebral palsy, which means he needs intensive, hospital-level care at home. Josue cannot sit up by himself, does not speak, and uses a feeding tube. Most of his days are spent in the same room because of his medical needs.</p><p>Still, something powerful fills that small space: unwavering love. His mother, a dedicated single parent, always cares for him as his caregiver, advocate, and source of comfort. She hardly ever leaves his side and even sleeps in his room every night so she can watch over him and help whenever he needs it.</p><p>Josue’s world may be small now, but with the right support, it can grow.</p>",
